 width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1558<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 10:30:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3463.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help with Miragul Location</span><hr size=1> Best bet is to ask your guild shamans if any of them ever camped for their old quest helms. If so they know the cave that Miragul is in very well. It is the same place as the bear they needed.<br><br>I have never seen a map of everfrost that was any good.<br><br>Your best bet is really finding out who in your guild is old school enough to have played a Barbarian and have LEARNED everfrost. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 10:53:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3463.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help with Miragul Location</span><hr size=1> The ice-covered river in Everfrost is in the shape of a Y.  The underwater caves are located at the top of the left branch (North end of West branch if you prefer directions) of the Y.  <br><br>EQAtlas has a map of the underwater caves and of Everfrost, but doesn't point out where the holes in the ice are.  It does provide the loc of the cave entrance which is approximately +3500, -4000.<br><br>You can't just go to the cave entrance though, you need to find a hole in the ice and then swim to the cave entrance.  The cave itself is not underwater, and if you know where you're going and swim fast enough you don't need Enduring Breath to get there (probably better safe than sorry though with people who have never been there).<br><br>The loc of a nearby hole in the ice is at +1400, -4600.  Drop into the water there and swim North to the cave entrance.<br><br>The Lich of Miragul wanders the caves.  If you keep your party in the first passageway before the first intersection they won't aggro it early--the Lich's roaming path does go right through that intersection though. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A> at: 4/15/02 11:06:04 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uapostyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apostyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 11:48:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3463.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Help with Miragul Location</span><hr size=1> I found him just